Subject: [PATCH] feat(campaign-3.0): card chrome + mobile parity (rounds
 44-46.24)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

S1 floating card visual cleanup (extended debugging chain landing on):
- 1px solid #e5e5ea border via two-fill technique (outer rect 1px
  larger than inner white card — avoids canvas2D stroke() AA fighting
  with surrounding pixels)
- radius 5/6 corners (small enough that corner AA mismatch with the
  straight edges falls under visual detection threshold)
- material.premultipliedAlpha=true on the card planes so scene→RT
  blend preserves straight-alpha and the shader's mix() composite
  resolves cleanly at the alpha edge (no grey ring)
- shadowPad pad area now filled with the shadow halo color so GPU
  bilinear interp between border texels and pad doesn't produce
  grey
- canvas2D drop-shadow dropped entirely — diagnostic confirmed it
  produced asymmetric darkness through the WebGL pipeline that no
  parameter tuning resolved (pixel probe values went uniform on all
  4 sides immediately after dropping it)
- plane positions snapped to integer device pixels for clean
  texture→screen rasterization
- CA strength bumped 0.005 → 0.020 (4x) so chromatic aberration
  reads clearly across card boundaries and headline text at section
  edges
- film grain gated by smoothstep(0.15, 1.0, r²) — center clean, only
  section corners get the noise

S1 lens load race fix:
- THREE.js was moved to a deferred dynamic script tag by another
  task; inline lens IIFE was bailing out via typeof check before
  THREE loaded. Replaced with polling waitForThree(initLens) +
  10s ceiling.

Mobile parity (≤760px):
- phone media block restructured by section (nav / S1 / S2 / S3 /
  S4 / footer / modals)
- S3 leaderboard table: new 4-col grid (22 / 1fr / 58 / 52) so ROI
  + Risk pills no longer clip at 390px; .who wrapper div gets
  min-width:0 / flex:1 / overflow:hidden so name + handle actually
  ellipsize
- S2 stage marquee: desktop's 1250px backdrop-blur mask used to
  dim the entire phone viewport; on mobile the overlay is normal
  flow with no mask and stage resets from flex to block
- S1 hero: H1 halo retuned for narrow viewport, tweet density
  dropped to 4, WebGL lens pass skipped entirely (battery + visual
  payoff disappears at phone widths)
- S4 carousel cards reflow to calc(100vw - 56px)
- Modals: tight padding, full-width primary + ghost CTAs
- New 380px sub-breakpoint for iPhone SE-class screens
